snippet.title: Canon in D - Johann Pachelbel
snippet.description:
"Canon in D," by Johann Pachelbel, is a classical piece recognized for its gentle melody and harmonious structure. Originally composed for three violins and continuo, the music is appreciated for its timeless beauty. When performed on the piano, its rich harmony and charming melodic patterns remain, offering an engaging and emotional musical experience.

snippet.title: Chopin - Waltz in B minor, Op. 69, No. 2
snippet.description:
Chopin's Waltz Op. 69, No. 2, also known as the "Farewell Waltz," is a captivating and emotive musical piece. Composed in the early 1830s, it is characterized by its delicate and flowing melody, along with its engaging harmonies. This waltz is an expression of tenderness and nostalgia, conveying a sense of gentle, melancholic farewell. Chopin's ability to create a rich emotional atmosphere through his music is evident in this piece, making it one of the most cherished and iconic works in the repertoire of romantic piano music.

Performed by Gabriel piano

snippet.title: After Dark X The PERFECT Girl (Public Piano Cover)
snippet.description:
I was on vacation in Rio De Janeiro (Brazil) and I hadn't played the piano for about 2 weeks… until I found this piano in the center of the city and decided to play it :) 

🎹“As the hours pass
I will let you know
That I need to ask
Before I'm alone..” 

🎹” You're such a strange girl 
I think you come from another world
